import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['date'])
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='wounds', data=data, ax=ax, label='wounds')
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='other', data=data, ax=ax, label='other')
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='disease', data=data, ax=ax, label='disease')
    plt.title('What is the trend of wounds, other and disease over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='wounds', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['wounds'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['wounds'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wounds?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
